doc_summary_long: New York City will have to pay out $180,000 to three Muslim women after forcing them to take off their hijabs for mugshots. Three lawsuits were settled Monday in Brooklyn federal court stemming from the NYPD policy of photographing people wearing religious head coverings, the New York Daily News reported. The three women settled for $60,000 each.
doc_summary_short: New York City will have to pay out $180,000 to three Muslim women after forcing them to take off their hijabs for mugshots.
doc_title: NYC must pay $180G to 3 Muslim women forced to remove hijabs for mugshots
